functionEntry.name: onTimerStart
functionEntry.documentation:
The activity timer has started.
This method is called when the activity timer goes from a stopped state to a started state.
If the activity timer is running when the app is loaded, this event will run immediately after startup.

functionEntry.name: onTimerReset
functionEntry.documentation:
The current activity has ended.
This method is called when the time has stopped and current activity is ended.

functionEntry.name: onTimerResume
functionEntry.documentation:
The activity time has resumed.
This method is called when the activity timer goes from a paused state to a running state.

functionEntry.name: onTimerPause
functionEntry.documentation:
The activity timer is paused.
This method is called when the activity timer goes from a running state to a paused state.
The paused state occurs when the auto-pause feature pauses the timer.
If the activity timer is paused when the app is loaded, this event will run immediately after startup.

functionEntry.name: onTimerStop
functionEntry.documentation:
The activity timer has stopped.
This method is called when the activity timer goes from a running state to a stopped state.

functionEntry.name: fixScanState
functionEntry.documentation:
Try to fix the scan state if it was in error.
For example, if the scan state has been set to
Toybox.BluetoothLowEnergy.SCAN_STATE_SCANNING
but the profiles have not been properly registered,
it will try to switch to Toybox.BluetoothLowEnergy.SCAN_STATE_OFF
and a second call will switch back to Toybox.BluetoothLowEnergy.SCAN_STATE_SCANNING

You should call this function periodically if you didn't get a success in onScanStateChange.
Call it periodically with some interval to let the bluetooth work properly.

Returns True if we tried to fix an error and false if there was no error to fix.

functionEntry.name: disconnect
functionEntry.documentation:
Disconnect and unpair from all paired devices. Normally, there should always be at most one
but to be sure to disconnect from any devices, we unpair every paired devices.

Returns false if there was no device to unpaired, true otherwise.

functionEntry.name: connect
functionEntry.documentation:
Connect and pair to a scanned device. It will first turn off scanning and
disconnect from other device. This is for consistency since we don't allow
multiple device to be connected at once.
Then it tries to pair with the device.
On error, it will call the delegate onError method with
the caught exception from the pairing operation or with a
Toybox.System.PreviousOperationNotCompleteException if the pairing could
not be completed for unknown reason.

scanResult The service uuid.


Returns true if the operation was successful, false otherwise.
